OL,3,CFamilies 'trying to survive instead of
OL,4,Cthrive' amid childcare crisis
OL,6,F"Families are trying to survive
OL,7,Finstead of thrive.
OL,9,F"If the government got it right and
OL,10,Finvested in childcare, the ripple
OL,11,Feffect of that: if families have
OL,12,Fsupport with childcare bills they're
OL,13,Fable to work more, progress their
OL,14,Fcareer, have more disposable income,
OL,15,Fwhich will then get invested back in
OL,16,Fthe economy.
OL,18,F"The positive ripple effect of
OL,19,Finvesting in childcare for the whole
OL,20,Fof society is endless."
